  "rationale": "<p style=\"text-align: left;\">Choice A is correct. The volume, <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"upper V\"><mi>V</mi></math>, of a rectangular prism is given by the formula <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"upper V equals script l w h\"><mi>V</mi><mo>=</mo><mi mathvariant=\"script\">l</mi><mi>w</mi><mi>h</mi></math>, where <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"script l\"><mi mathvariant=\"script\">l</mi></math> is the length of the base, <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"w\"><mi>w</mi></math> is the width of the base, and <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"h\"><mi>h</mi></math> is the height of the prism. It&rsquo;s given that each base of a right rectangular prism has a length of <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"19\"><mn>19</mn></math> inches and a width of <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"8\"><mn>8</mn></math> inches, and that the prism has a volume of <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"2,736\"><mn>2,736</mn></math> cubic inches. Substituting <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"19\"><mn>19</mn></math> for <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"script l\"><mi mathvariant=\"script\">l</mi></math>, <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"8\"><mn>8</mn></math> for <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"w\"><mi>w</mi></math>, and <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"2,736\"><mn>2,736</mn></math> for <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"upper V\"><mi>V</mi></math> in the formula <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"upper V equals script l w h\"><mi>V</mi><mo>=</mo><mi mathvariant=\"script\">l</mi><mi>w</mi><mi>h</mi></math> gives <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"2,736 equals left parenthesis 19 right parenthesis left parenthesis 8 right parenthesis left parenthesis h right parenthesis\"><mn>2,736</mn><mo>=</mo><mo>(</mo><mn>19</mn><mo>)</mo><mo>(</mo><mn>8</mn><mo>)</mo><mo>(</mo><mi>h</mi><mo>)</mo></math>, or <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"2,736 equals 152 h\"><mn>2,736</mn><mo>=</mo><mn>152</mn><mi>h</mi></math>. Dividing each side of this equation by <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"152\"><mn>152</mn></math> yields <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"18 equals h\"><mn>18</mn><mo>=</mo><mi>h</mi></math>. Therefore, the height, in inches, of the prism is <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"18\"><mn>18</mn></math>.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">Choice B is incorrect and may result from conceptual or calculation errors.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">Choice C is incorrect and may result from conceptual or calculation errors.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">Choice D is incorrect. This is the area, in square inches, of the base of the prism, not the height, in inches, of the prism.</p>",
